<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="355" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="355">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[862,924,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="355">mono</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis box="[991,1100,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="355">processus</emphasis>
, referring to the valva with a square process only at left.
</paragraph>
